messages.msgSnippet: It s not at yahoogroups under unschcooling OR unschooling. Find the home page of your group by going to
messages.messageBody:
<< LDSunshcooling-subscribe@yahoogroups.com >>

It's not at yahoogroups under unschcooling OR unschooling.

Find the home page of your group by going to yahoogroups and double check
what you named it.

Of if the home page won't come up, maybe the make-a-list didn't quite take.

43 groups came up searching for LDS homeschool, but not all were strictly
just LDS groups. Many were. Most are small, but there are a few bigger ones.


Searching, I found this:


HISHOUSEFULL
This list is for Christian Women only, who have five or more children. Any
Protestant or Catholic women, NO Mormon, or LDS faith is represented here.
All children must be biological, not adopted, no foster children. The reason
for this is we are ladies who want to share stories of birthing many
children, being pregnant while breastfeeding, and encourage one another in
the area of letting the womb be controlled by the Lord. In adoption, the womb
is not affected, and fostering children is not part ... more

They have more than five kids but there are fewer than 5 members on their
group. <g>


Sandra
